  schema:name "Valerianella locusta" ;
  schema:description "Winter annual from Caprifoliaceae (formerly Valerianaceae), native to Mediterranean and Middle East. Produces low rosette of spoon-shaped, smooth leaves; exceptionally frost-hardy to 5–10°F. Seed exhibits deep dormancy above 68°F; ideal cool-season crop for fall through spring cultivation." ;
